2 HOUSE BILL 1325
1 (2) “CHILD CARE FACILITY” MEANS:
2 (I) A LICENSED CHILD CARE CENTER;
3 (II) A REGISTERED FAMILY CHILD CARE HOME; OR
4 (III) A REGISTERED LARGE FAMILY CHILD CARE HOME.
5 (3) “CHILD CARE PROVIDER” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO PROVIDES
6 CARE FOR A CHILD IN A CHILD CARE FACILITY.
7 (4) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDER
8 POOL PILOT PROGRAM.
9 (5) “SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDER POOL” MEANS ONE OR
10 MORE CHILD CARE PROVIDERS WHO ARE AVAILABLE TO PROVIDE TEMPORARY CARE
11 TO CHILDREN AS A SUBSTITUTE FOR A REGULAR CHILD CARE PROVIDER IN A CHILD
12 CARE FACILITY AND WHO:
13 (I) HAVE THE REQUIRED CREDENTIALS, TRAINING,
14 EXPERIENCE, AND CRIMINAL HISTORY VETTING TO WORK IN A CHILD CARE
15 FACILITY; AND
16 (II) ARE LOCATED IN THE SAME REGION OF THE STATE AS THE
17 CHILD CARE FACILITY PARTICIPATING IN THE PROGRAM.
18 (B) (1) THERE IS A SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDER POOL PILOT
19 PROGRAM IN THE DEPARTMENT.
20 (2) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO FACILITATE THE
21 CONTINUOUS OPERATION OF CHILD CARE FACILITIES IN THE STATE BY ENSURING
22 THAT QUALIFIED SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDERS ARE AVAILABLE TO FILL
23 SHORT–TERM STAFFING NEEDS OF CHILD CARE FACILITIES ON A TEMPORARY BASIS.
24 (3) THE PROGRAM SHALL BEGIN JULY 1, 2026, AND END JUNE 30,
25 2030 2028.
26 (C) (1) (I) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL SELECT A NONPROFIT
27 ORGANIZATION TO ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM THAT MEETS THE REQUIREMENTS
28 OF THIS SUBSECTION.
29 (II) FOR EACH OF FISCAL YEARS 2027 THROUGH 2030 AND
30 2028, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL AWARD A GRANT OF $350,000 $50,000 TO THE
31 NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION SELECTED TO ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM.

HOUSE BILL 1325 3
1 (2) TO BE ELIGIBLE TO ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM AND RECEIVE A
2 GRANT UNDER THIS SECTION, A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION SHALL:
3 (I) BE A PUBLIC BENEFIT CORPORATION THAT IS EXEMPT
4 FROM TAXATION AS PROVIDED BY LAW;
5 (II) OPERATE THROUGHOUT THE STATE;
6 (III) HAVE EXPERIENCE WORKING WITH CHILD CARE FACILITIES
7 OF ALL TYPES; AND
8 (IV) HAVE EXPERIENCE HELPING INDIVIDUALS MEET THE
9 LEGAL REQUIREMENTS TO WORK AS CHILD CARE PROVIDERS.
10 (D) THE NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION SELECTED BY THE DEPARTMENT
11 SHALL USE THE GRANT TO:
12 (1) ORGANIZE A SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDER POOLS POOL IN
13 AT LEAST THREE REGIONS ONE REGION IN THE STATE, INCLUDING A RURAL,
14 SUBURBAN, AND URBAN AREA;
15 (2) RECRUIT CREDENTIALED CHILD CARE PROVIDERS TO PROVIDE
16 SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE SERVICES IN MULTIPLE CHILD CARE FACILITIES
17 PARTICIPATING IN THE PROGRAM;
18 (3) ASSIST A SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDER WITH MEETING THE
19 REQUIREMENTS TO WORK IN A CHILD CARE FACILITY, INCLUDING BY HELPING THE
20 SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDER:
21 (I) OBTAIN A CRIMINAL HISTORY RECORDS CHECK, AS
22 REQUIRED UNDER § 5–551 OF THE FAMILY LAW ARTICLE, AS AN EMPLOYEE, A
23 CONTRACTOR, OR A SUBCONTRACTOR OF THE CHILD CARE FACILITY;
24 (II) MEET ANY EXPERIENTIAL OR EDUCATIONAL
25 REQUIREMENTS; AND
26 (III) COMPLETE ANY REQUIRED TRAINING, INCLUDING HEALTH
27 AND SAFETY TRAINING AND FIRST AID TRAINING;
28 (4) TO THE EXTENT PRACTICABLE, ASSIST A SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE
29 PROVIDER IN COMPLETING A REGISTERED EARLY EDUCATION APPRENTICESHIP;

4 HOUSE BILL 1325
1 (5) IDENTIFY AND ORGANIZE, INTO REGIONAL AREAS, CHILD CARE
2 FACILITIES THAT AGREE TO WORK WITH SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDERS FROM
3 A POOL ESTABLISHED BY THE PROGRAM;
4 (6) KEEP ANY RECORDS REQUIRED BY THE DEPARTMENT; AND
5 (7) COMPLY WITH ANY OTHER REQUIREMENTS ESTABLISHED BY THE
6 DEPARTMENT.
7 (E) THE NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION SELECTED BY THE DEPARTMENT MAY
8 USE THE GRANT TO:
9 (1) CREATE A STATEWIDE DIGITAL PLATFORM TO FACILITATE THE
10 MATCHING OF SUBSTITUTE CHILD CARE PROVIDERS FROM THE SUBSTITUTE CHILD
11 CARE PROVIDER POOL WITH PARTICIPATING CHILD CARE FACILITIES, INCLUDING
12 PARTNERING WITH A THIRD–PARTY VENDOR; AND
13 (2) INCENTIVIZE PARTICIPATION IN THE PROGRAM BY QUALIFIED
14 CHILD CARE PROVIDERS AND CHILD CARE FACILITIES.
15 (F) FOR EACH OF FISCAL YEARS 2027 THROUGH 2030 AND 2028, THE
16 GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF
17 $375,000 $50,000 FOR THE PROGRAM.
18 (G) EACH YEAR THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DEVELOP AND PUBLISH GOALS
19 FOR THE PROGRAM.
20 (H) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1, 2029 2027, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL
21 REPORT TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE
22 STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, ON THE STATUS OF THE PROGRAM, INCLUDING:
23 (1) AN EVALUATION OF THE PROGRAM; AND
24 (2) WHETHER THE PROGRAM HAS MET THE GOALS SET BY THE
25 DEPARTMENT.
26 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
27 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of 5 3 years and, at the end of June 30, 2030
28 2028, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be abrogated
29 and of no further force and effect.

